{
    "cells": [
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"kql-for-email-security-beginner-series\" name=\"kql-for-email-security-beginner-series\"></a>\r\n# KQL for Email Security — Beginner Series\r\n\r\nLearn to hunt threats in Microsoft 365 email using Kusto Query Languag (KQL)\r\n\r\n**Where to run these queries:** [Microsoft Defender portal](https://security.microsoft.com) → Investigation & response → Hunting → Advanced hunting\r\n\r\n### Sample Tables\r\n| Table | What It Tells You |\r\n|-------|------------------|\r\n| `EmailEvents` | Every email that touched your org |\r\n| `EmailAttachmentInfo` | Files attached to those emails |\r\n| `EmailUrlInfo` | Links embedded in emails |\r\n| `UrlClickEvents` | Who clicked what, and when |\r\n| `EmailPostDeliveryEvents` | What happened after delivery (ZAP, moves, deletes) |\r\n| `IdentityLogonEvents` | User sign-ins and authentication |\r\n| `CloudAppEvents` | User actions in cloud apps (Exchange, SharePoint, etc.) |\r\n\r\n<br>",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"toc\" name=\"toc\"></a>\r\n# Table of Contents\r\n\r\n1. [Table Relationships Quick Reference](#table-relationships-quick-reference)\r\n2. [getschema](#getschema)\r\n3. [print](#print)\r\n4. [comments ( // )](#comments)\r\n5. [pipe ( | )](#pipe)\r\n6. [spacing](#spacing)\r\n7. [order matters](#order-matters)\r\n8. [search](#search)\r\n9. [take / limit / sample](#take-limit-sample)\r\n10. [where](#where)\r\n11. [== / != (equality operators)](#equality-operators)\r\n12. [and / or / in](#and-or-in)\r\n13. [tilde ( ~ )](#tilde)\r\n14. [project](#project)\r\n15. [project-away / project-reorder](#project-away-project-reorder)\r\n16. [distinct](#distinct)\r\n17. [sort by](#sort-by)\r\n18. [contains / has / startswith / endswith](#contains-has-startswith-endswith)\r\n19. [negation ( ! )](#negation)\r\n20. [count](#count)\r\n21. [>, <, >=, <= (numeric comparisons)](#comparison-operators)\r\n22. [ago()](#ago)\r\n23. [between / datetime](#between-datetime)\r\n24. [Time Formats](#time-formats)\r\n25. [now()](#now)\r\n26. [top](#top)\r\n27. [extend](#extend)\r\n28. [Live Scenario: EmailAttachmentInfo](#live-scenario-emailattachmentinfo)\r\n29. [Live Scenario: EmailEvents](#live-scenario-emailevents)\r\n30. [Live Scenario: CloudAppEvents](#live-scenario-cloudappevents)\r\n31. [Live Scenario: UrlClickEvents](#live-scenario-urlclickevents)\r\n32. [Live Scenario: EmailPostDeliveryEvents](#live-scenario-emailpostdeliveryevents)\r\n33. [Common Gotchas & Tips](#common-gotchas-tips)\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"table-relationships-quick-reference\" name=\"table-relationships-quick-reference\"></a>\r\n## Table Relationships Quick Reference\r\n\r\nUnderstanding how tables relate is critical for effective hunting:\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25; white-space: pre;\">\r\n┌─────────────────┐     NetworkMessageId      ┌─────────────────────┐\r\n│   EmailEvents   │◄──────────────────────────│ EmailAttachmentInfo │\r\n│                 │                           └─────────────────────┘\r\n│  (Core email    │     NetworkMessageId      ┌─────────────────────┐\r\n│   metadata)     │◄──────────────────────────│    EmailUrlInfo     │\r\n│                 │                           └─────────────────────┘\r\n│                 │     NetworkMessageId      ┌─────────────────────────┐\r\n│                 │◄──────────────────────────│ EmailPostDeliveryEvents │\r\n└─────────────────┘                           └─────────────────────────┘\r\n        │\r\n        │ RecipientEmailAddress / AccountUpn\r\n        ▼\r\n┌─────────────────────┐         AccountUpn / AccountObjectId         ┌──────────────────┐\r\n│ IdentityLogonEvents │◄─────────────────────────────────────────────│  CloudAppEvents  │\r\n│ (Sign-ins)          │                                              │ (User actions)   │\r\n└─────────────────────┘                                              └──────────────────┘\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**Key Join Fields:**\r\n- `NetworkMessageId` — Links all email-related tables\r\n- `AccountUpn` / `RecipientEmailAddress` — Links email to identity tables\r\n- `AccountObjectId` — Links identity events to cloud app events\r\n",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"getschema\" name=\"getschema\"></a>\r\n## getschema\r\n\r\n- Displays column names and data types for tables.\r\n- Essential for discovering what data is available.\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailEvents | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "IdentityLogonEvents | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "CloudAppEvents | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailAttachmentInfo | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailUrlInfo | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "UrlClickEvents | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailPostDeliveryEvents | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "AlertInfo | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "AlertEvidence | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EntraSignInEvents | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EntraSpnSignInEvents | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "IdentityInfo | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "MessageEvents | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "MessagePostDeliveryEvents | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "MessageUrlInfo | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"print\" name=\"print\"></a>\r\n## print\r\n\r\n- Use `print` to test expressions without querying tables.\r\n- Great for learning time functions, string manipulation, etc.\r\n- \r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Test time expressions\r\nprint CurrentTime = now(), OneWeekAgo = ago(7d), OneDayAgo = ago(1d)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Test string functions\r\nprint \r\n    Original = \"user@CONTOSO.com\",\r\n    Lower = tolower(\"user@CONTOSO.com\"),\r\n    Upper = toupper(\"user@contoso.com\")",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Test math expressions\r\nprint \r\n    BytesToKB = 1048576 / 1024,\r\n    BytesToMB = 1048576 / 1024 / 1024",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Test conditional expressions\r\nprint\r\n    IsHighSeverity = iff(\"High\" == \"High\", true, false),\r\n    SeverityLabel = case(\r\n        \"High\" == \"High\", \"🔴 High\",\r\n        \"High\" == \"Medium\", \"🟡 Medium\",\r\n        \"🟢 Low\"\r\n    )",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Test strcat — useful for building display strings\r\nprint\r\n    AlertSummary  = strcat(\"[ALERT] \", \"Suspicious sign-in\", \" — Severity: High\"),\r\n    BehaviorLabel = strcat(\"User: \", \"bob@contoso.com\", \" | Action: \", \"LateralMovement\")",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Test dynamic arrays — used in AttackTechniques and ThreatTypes\r\nprint\r\n    Techniques   = dynamic([\"T1078\", \"T1059\", \"T1003\"]),\r\n    FirstTech    = tostring(dynamic([\"T1078\", \"T1059\"])[0]),\r\n    TechCount    = array_length(dynamic([\"T1078\", \"T1059\", \"T1003\"]))",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"comments\" name=\"comments\"></a>\r\n## comments ( // )\r\n\r\n- Use `//` to add inline comments to queries.\r\n- Helps document your logic for future reference.\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Show last 10 email events\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Look at recent sign-ins\r\nIdentityLogonEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n// | where Application == \"Microsoft SharePoint Online\"  // Uncomment to filter by app\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Browse recent Entra sign-in events\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n// | where ErrorCode != 0  // Uncomment to filter failures only\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Browse recent security alerts\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n// | where Severity == \"High\"  // Uncomment to filter by severity\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Browse Teams message events\r\nMessageEvents\r\n| take 10\r\n// MessageEvents = Teams messages scanned by Defender for Office 365",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Browse identity info for a user\r\nIdentityInfo\r\n// | where AccountUpn =~ \"user@contoso.com\"  // Uncomment and set UPN\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"pipe\" name=\"pipe\"></a>\r\n## pipe ( | )\r\n\r\n- The pipe passes data from one operation to the next.\r\n- Read queries top-to-bottom, left-to-right.\r\n\r\n**How pipe works**\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25;\">\r\nEmailEvents                               ← Start: All rows from table\r\n      │\r\n      ▼\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)               ← Filter: Keep only last 7 days\r\n      │\r\n      ▼\r\n| where SenderFromDomain has \"x\"          ← Filter: Keep matching domains\r\n      │\r\n      ▼\r\n| project Subject, SenderFromAddress      ← Select: Keep only these columns\r\n      │\r\n      ▼\r\n| take 10                                 ← Limit: Return first 10 rows\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailEvents\r\n| where SenderFromDomain == \"gmail.com\"\r\n| project Subject, SenderFromAddress, RecipientEmailAddress",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "IdentityLogonEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n// | where Application has \"Office\"\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, Location",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "CloudAppEvents\r\n| where ActionType == \"FileDownloaded\"\r\n| take 5\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountDisplayName, ActionType, Application",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Sign-in failures piped to clean output\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| where ErrorCode != 0\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, IPAddress, Country, ErrorCode",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Alert evidence filtered to user entities only\r\nAlertEvidence\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where EntityType == \"User\"\r\n| project Timestamp, AlertId, AccountUpn, EvidenceRole, RemoteIP",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Teams message URLs — browse what URLs are being sent\r\nMessageUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project Timestamp, TeamsMessageId, Url, UrlDomain\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// EmailUrlInfo — URLs piped to distinct domains\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| distinct UrlDomain\r\n| sort by UrlDomain asc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// UrlClickEvents — blocked clicks piped to clean output\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType == \"ClickBlocked\"\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, IsClickedThrough",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// EmailPostDeliveryEvents — ZAP actions piped to summary\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType has \"ZAP\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, DeliveryLocation",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// EmailAttachmentInfo — suspicious extensions piped to count\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where FileExtension in (\".exe\", \".ps1\", \".vbs\", \".bat\")\r\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, FileName, FileExtension",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"spacing\" name=\"spacing\"></a>\r\n## spacing\r\n\r\n- KQL ignores extra spaces and newlines.\r\n- Indentation improves readability for complex queries.\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailEvents\r\n| where\r\n    SenderFromDomain has \"gmail\"\r\n    and DeliveryLocation has \"Inbox\"\r\n| project Subject,\r\n    RecipientEmailAddress, NetworkMessageId\r\n| take                                                                                                                        5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Spacing makes multi-condition filters readable\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where\r\n    Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n    and Severity == \"High\"\r\n    and ServiceSource has \"Defender\"\r\n| project Timestamp,\r\n    AlertId, Title, Severity, Category\r\n| take                                                 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"order-matters\" name=\"order-matters\"></a>\n## order matters\n\nKQL executes each pipe stage **left to right, top to bottom** — the output of one stage becomes the input of the next. That means the earlier you reduce the dataset, the less work every later stage has to do.\n\n**Mental Model:**\n1. **Time filter first** — shrinks the dataset at the source using the built-in time index\n2. **Column filters next** — narrow rows on indexed/selective columns\n3. **Shape last** — `project`, `extend`, `distinct`, `sort` operate on what survived\n\nGet wide data narrow *before* doing expensive operations on it.",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "---\r\n\r\n**Scenario 1: find high-severity MDO alerts from the last 7 days**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 1 — Start with the table\n// Every query starts here. No filters yet — this would return ALL data.\nAlertInfo",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 2 — Add the time filter FIRST\n// Timestamp is indexed. This one filter can eliminate millions of rows before anything else runs.\n// Always your first where clause.\nAlertInfo\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 3 — Add a column filter SECOND\n// Now we narrow to just High severity rows — but only from the 7-day window we already scoped.\n// The engine never touches older rows at all.\nAlertInfo\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where Severity == \"High\"",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 4 — Add a second column filter before any shaping\n// Still filtering, not yet reshaping. More rows eliminated cheaply.\nAlertInfo\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where Severity == \"High\"\n| where ServiceSource == \"AAD Identity Protection\"",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 5 — Shape the output with project\n// project runs last, on only the rows that survived all filters.\n// If project ran first, it would process every row in the table.\nAlertInfo\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where Severity == \"High\"\n| where ServiceSource == \"AAD Identity Protection\"\n| project Timestamp, Title, Category, ServiceSource",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 6 — Final query: sort and limit at the very end\n// sort and take are the most expensive per-row operations.\n// Running them on 20 rows is trivial. Running them on millions is not.\nAlertInfo\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where Severity == \"High\"\n| where ServiceSource == \"AAD Identity Protection\"\n| project Timestamp, Title, Category, ServiceSource\n| sort by Timestamp desc\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "**What happens if you get the order wrong?**\n\n`project` before `where` is the most common mistake. Here's why it hurts:\n\n<pre style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25;\">\n┌─────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────┐\n│ Inefficient order:          │ Efficient order:             │\n├─────────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────┤\n│ AlertInfo                   │ AlertInfo                    │\n│ | project Title, Severity   │ | where Timestamp > ago(7d)  │\n│ | where Timestamp > ago(7d) │ | where Severity == \"High\"   │\n│ | where Severity == \"High\"  │ | project Title, Severity    │\n└─────────────────────────────┴──────────────────────────────┘\n</pre>\n\nIn the inefficient version, `project` reshapes **every row in the table** before the time filter even runs.  \nIn the efficient version, the time filter eliminates the vast majority of rows before `project` ever sees them.",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "---\r\n\r\n**Scenario 2: finding inbound emails with attachments from external senders**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 1 — Start with the table\n// EmailEvents holds every email event in the tenant — potentially millions of rows.\nEmailEvents",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 2 — Time filter first (always)\n// The Timestamp index makes this the cheapest possible filter.\n// Everything outside 7 days is gone before any other work happens.\nEmailEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 3 — Filter by direction\n// \"Inbound\" likely cuts the dataset roughly in half.\n// Still just a row filter — no shaping yet.\nEmailEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where EmailDirection == \"Inbound\"",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 4 — Filter to emails that actually have attachments\n// AttachmentCount > 0 eliminates the majority of inbound email.\n// We're now working with a much smaller set before doing anything expensive.\nEmailEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where EmailDirection == \"Inbound\"\n| where AttachmentCount > 0",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 5 — extend adds a derived column AFTER all row filtering\n// If it ran before the filters, it would compute on the entire table.\nEmailEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where EmailDirection == \"Inbound\"\n| where AttachmentCount > 0\n| extend AttachmentRisk = case(\n    AttachmentCount > 5, \"High\",\n    AttachmentCount > 1, \"Medium\",\n    \"Low\")",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Step 6 — Final query: project and sort last\n// project selects only the columns we need — on the smallest possible row set.\n// sort runs last, on already-filtered, already-shaped output.\nEmailEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where EmailDirection == \"Inbound\"\n| where AttachmentCount > 0\n| extend AttachmentRisk = case(\n    AttachmentCount > 5, \"High\",\n    AttachmentCount > 1, \"Medium\",\n    \"Low\")\n| project Timestamp, AttachmentRisk, RecipientEmailAddress, Subject, AttachmentCount\n| sort by Timestamp desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "**The rule of thumb:**\n\n| Stage | What to do | Why |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1st `where` | `Timestamp > ago(Xd)` | Uses the time index — free row elimination |\n| 2nd `where` | Most selective column filter | Eliminates the most rows cheapest |\n| 3rd+ `where` | Additional column filters | Keep narrowing before any computation |\n| `distinct` | Deduplicate | After filters, before sort — never sort duplicates you're about to drop |\n| `extend` | Computed/derived columns | Only compute on rows that survived |\n| `project` | Shape the output | Runs on the smallest possible set |\n| `sort` / `take` | Ordering and limits | Always last — most expensive per row |\n\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Efficient — filter before projection\nEmailEvents\n| where SenderFromDomain == \"gmail.com\"\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, Subject",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Inefficient — projection before filtering\nEmailEvents\n// | where Timestamp >= ago(7d)\n| project SenderFromDomain, Subject\n| where SenderFromDomain == \"gmail.com\"",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Efficient — distinct then sort (dedupe before sort)\nEmailEvents\n| distinct SenderFromDomain\n| sort by SenderFromDomain desc\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Less efficient — sort everything first, then dedupe\nEmailEvents\n| sort by SenderFromDomain\n| distinct SenderFromDomain\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Efficient — filter before projection\nIdentityLogonEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\n| where Application == \"Microsoft 365\"\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Location, Application",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Inefficient — expensive extend before filtering\n// extend computes strcat for every row\n// many of those rows get discarded by the where clauses after\nIdentityLogonEvents\n| extend Geo = strcat(Location, \"-\", AccountUpn)\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\n| where Application == \"Microsoft 365\"\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Location, Geo",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Efficient — time filter first on Entra sign-ins\nEntraSignInEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)   // ← filter early\n| where ErrorCode != 0\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, IPAddress, ErrorCode",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Inefficient — project before filter wastes work\n// all rows flow through project before the ErrorCode filter\nEntraSignInEvents\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, IPAddress, ErrorCode\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\n| where ErrorCode != 0",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Efficient — filter alerts before extending labels\nAlertInfo\n// | where Timestamp > ago(7d)           // ← filter first\n| where Severity == \"High\"            // ← second filter\n| extend SevTag = strcat(\"[\", Severity, \"] \", Title)  // extend after\n| project Timestamp, SevTag, Category, ServiceSource",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Efficient — filter before distinct, distinct before count\nIdentityInfo\n| where IsAccountEnabled == true   // ← filter before distinct\n| distinct Department\n| count",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\n\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"search\" name=\"search\"></a>\r\n## search\r\n\r\n- Full-text search across all columns.\r\n- Use for quick exploration, not production queries.\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "search \"facebook\"",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Search within specific tables\r\nsearch in (IdentityLogonEvents, CloudAppEvents) \"failed\"",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "search in (EmailEvents, CloudAppEvents)\r\n \"facebook\"\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(24h)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "search in (CloudAppEvents)\r\n \"groupon\"\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| take 100",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Search alert tables for a specific MITRE technique\r\nsearch in (AlertInfo, AlertEvidence) \"T1078\"\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Search identity tables for a suspicious IP address\r\nsearch in (EntraSignInEvents, IdentityLogonEvents) \"185.220.101.1\"\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Search Teams message tables for malicious content\r\nsearch in (MessageEvents, MessageUrlInfo) \"malware\"\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Search EmailUrlInfo for a suspicious domain\r\nsearch in (EmailUrlInfo) \"malware-site.com\"\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Search UrlClickEvents for a blocked action\r\nsearch in (UrlClickEvents) \"ClickBlocked\"\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Search EmailAttachmentInfo and EmailUrlInfo together\r\nsearch in (EmailAttachmentInfo, EmailUrlInfo) \"phish\"\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Search EmailPostDeliveryEvents for ZAP activity\r\nsearch in (EmailPostDeliveryEvents) \"ZAP\"\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"take-limit-sample\" name=\"take-limit-sample\"></a>\r\n## take / limit / sample\r\n\r\n- `take` / `limit` - Returns first N rows (same behavior)\r\n- `sample` - Returns N random rows\r\n\r\n**Difference: take vs sample**\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25;\">\r\n              EmailEvents (1000 rows)\r\n                    │\r\n        ┌───────────┴───────────┐\r\n        │                       │\r\n   | take 3                | sample 3\r\n        │                       │\r\n        ▼                       ▼\r\n┌─────────────┐         ┌─────────────┐\r\n│ Row 1       │         │ Row 847     │  ← random\r\n│ Row 2       │         │ Row 123     │  ← random\r\n│ Row 3       │         │ Row 592     │  ← random\r\n└─────────────┘         └─────────────┘\r\n  First 3 rows           Random 3 rows\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailEvents\r\n| take 25",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "IdentityLogonEvents | limit 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Sample gives random rows - great for exploring data variety\r\nCloudAppEvents | sample 1",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailAttachmentInfo | take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailUrlInfo | take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "UrlClickEvents | take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailPostDeliveryEvents \r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(24h)\r\n// | take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "AlertInfo | take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "AlertEvidence | take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "IdentityInfo | take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "MessageEvents | take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"where\" name=\"where\"></a>\r\n## where\r\n\r\n- Filters rows based on conditions.\r\n- Only rows where the condition is `true` pass through.\r\n\r\n**How `where` works**\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25;\">\r\nBefore: EmailEvents (all rows)\r\n┌──────────────┬─────────────────┬───────────────┐\r\n│ Subject      │ SenderDomain    │ Timestamp     │\r\n├──────────────┼─────────────────┼───────────────┤\r\n│ Invoice      │ external.com    │ 2024-01-15    │   passes\r\n│ Meeting      │ contoso.com     │ 2024-01-15    │   filtered\r\n│ Payment Due  │ external.com    │ 2024-01-14    │   passes\r\n│ Hello        │ contoso.com     │ 2024-01-14    │   filtered\r\n└──────────────┴─────────────────┴───────────────┘\r\n                      │\r\n    | where SenderDomain != \"contoso.com\"\r\n                      │\r\n                      ▼\r\nAfter: Only external emails\r\n┌──────────────┬─────────────────┬───────────────┐\r\n│ Invoice      │ external.com    │ 2024-01-15    │\r\n│ Payment Due  │ external.com    │ 2024-01-14    │\r\n└──────────────┴─────────────────┴───────────────┘\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(1d)\r\n| where EmailDirection == \"Inbound\"\r\n| where SenderFromDomain == \"yahoo.com\"\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Filter sign-ins by result\r\nIdentityLogonEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| where ActionType == \"LogonFailed\"\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Filter cloud events by action\r\nCloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| where ActionType has \"SoftDelete\"\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Find attachments with specific threat detections\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n// | where isnotempty(ThreatTypes)\r\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, RecipientEmailAddress, FileName, FileType, ThreatTypes, ThreatNames\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Find emails containing URLs from specific domains\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where UrlDomain has \"twitter\" or UrlDomain has \"facebook\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, Url, UrlDomain, UrlLocation\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailUrlInfo\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| where UrlLocation == \"Attachment\"\r\n// | where Url contains \"facebook\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, Url, UrlDomain, UrlLocation\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailUrlInfo\r\n| distinct UrlLocation",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "UrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n// | where ActionType == \"ClickBlocked\"\r\n// | project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, ActionType, ThreatTypes, Workload",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "UrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n// | where IsClickedThrough == true\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, ThreatTypes, Workload\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| where ActionType has \"ZAP\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, RecipientEmailAddress, ActionType, ActionTrigger, ActionResult, DeliveryLocation\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Find manual remediation actions by admins\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| where ActionType == \"Manual Remediation\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, RecipientEmailAddress, Action, ActionTrigger, ActionResult\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Filter Entra sign-in failures\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ErrorCode != 0\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, IPAddress, Country, ErrorCode\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Filter alerts to a specific detection service\r\nAlertInfo\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ServiceSource == \"Microsoft Defender for Office 365\"\r\n// | project Timestamp, AlertId, Title, Category, Severity\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Filter Teams messages where delivery was not clean\r\nMessageEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where DeliveryAction != \"Delivered\"\r\n| project Timestamp, TeamsMessageId, SenderEmailAddress, DeliveryAction, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Filter Entra service principal sign-in failures\r\nEntraSpnSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ErrorCode != 0\r\n| project Timestamp, ServicePrincipalName, ApplicationId, IPAddress, ErrorCode\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"equality-operators\" name=\"equality-operators\"></a>\r\n## == / != (equality operators)\r\n\r\n- `==` — exact match (case-sensitive)\r\n- `!=` — not equal\r\n- Used constantly inside `where` to filter by specific values.\r\n- For **case-insensitive** equality use `=~` — covered in the [tilde](#tilde) section.\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25;\">\r\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────┬─────────┐\r\n│ Expression                               │ Result  │\r\n├──────────────────────────────────────────┼─────────┤\r\n│ \"gmail.com\" == \"gmail.com\"               │ true    │\r\n│ \"gmail.com\" == \"Gmail.com\"               │ false   │\r\n│ \"gmail.com\" != \"yahoo.com\"               │ true    │\r\n│ \"gmail.com\" != \"gmail.com\"               │ false   │\r\n└──────────────────────────────────────────┴─────────┘\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exact match — only rows where EmailDirection is exactly \"Inbound\"\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where EmailDirection == \"Inbound\"\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// not equal — exclude outbound mail\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where EmailDirection != \"Outbound\"\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exact delivery location\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where DeliveryLocation == \"Inbox\"\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// case-sensitive\r\n// Use =~ if you're unsure of casing\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where EmailDirection == \"inbound\"  // returns 0 rows\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exclude a specific action type\r\nCloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType != \"FileAccessed\"\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountDisplayName, ActionType, Application\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// ErrorCode 0 means success in Entra sign-ins\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| where ErrorCode == 0\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, Country\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// non-zero ErrorCode means failure\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| where ErrorCode != 0\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, IPAddress, ErrorCode\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// filter to a specific alert severity\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Severity == \"High\"\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, Category, ServiceSource\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exclude a severity level\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Severity != \"Informational\"\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, Category\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// only rows for a specific entity kind\r\nAlertEvidence\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where EntityType == \"User\"\r\n| project Timestamp, AlertId, AccountUpn, EvidenceRole\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// only URLs embedded in the email body\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where UrlLocation == \"Body\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, Url, UrlDomain\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// only blocked clicks\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType == \"ClickBlocked\"\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, IsClickedThrough\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exclude manual remediation\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType != \"Manual Remediation\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, DeliveryLocation\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// only zip attachments\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where FileType == \"zip\"\r\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, FileName, FileType\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"and-or-in\" name=\"and-or-in\"></a>\r\n## and / or / in\r\n\r\n- Combine conditions.\r\n- `in` is cleaner than multiple `or` statements.\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Using 'in' for multiple values\nIdentityLogonEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where Application in (\"Microsoft 365\", \"Microsoft SharePoint Online\")\n| distinct Application, AccountUpn\n| sample 3",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Combining conditions\r\nCloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| where Application == \"Microsoft Exchange Online\" and ActionType has \"MoveToDeletedItems\"\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "CloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| where Application == \"Microsoft Exchange Online\"\r\n| where ActionType has \"MoveToDeletedItems\"\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "CloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d) \r\n    or Application == \"Microsoft Exchange Online\" \r\n    or ActionType has \"MoveToDeletedItems\"\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// NOT in - exclude values\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where SenderFromDomain !in (\"contoso.com\", \"microsoft.com\")\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailEvents \r\n| where Timestamp between (datetime(2026-01-02T19:05:00Z) .. datetime(2026-01-02T19:10:00Z))\r\n    and EmailDirection != 'Outbound'\r\n    and (RecipientDomain == 'contoso.com' or RecipientDomain == 'contoso.onmicrosoft.com')\r\n| project Timestamp, InternetMessageId, NetworkMessageId, RecipientEmailAddress, SenderFromAddress, Subject",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Using 'in' for multiple alert severity levels\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Severity in (\"High\", \"Medium\")\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, Category, ServiceSource\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Combining and — sign-in failures from outside the US\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ErrorCode != 0\r\n    and Country != \"US\"\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, IPAddress, Country, ErrorCode\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Using 'in' for multiple alert evidence entity types\r\nAlertEvidence\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where EntityType in (\"User\", \"Ip\", \"Url\")\r\n| project Timestamp, AlertId, EntityType, AccountUpn, RemoteIP\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// NOT in — exclude low-risk Entra error codes\r\n// 50125 = password reset, 50140 = keep me signed in\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ErrorCode !in (0, 50125, 50140)\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, IPAddress, ErrorCode\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// or — Teams messages with threats OR non-delivered\r\nMessageEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ThreatTypes != \"\"\r\n    or DeliveryAction != \"Delivered\"\r\n| project Timestamp, TeamsMessageId, SenderEmailAddress, DeliveryAction, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// and — URLs in body AND from external senders\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where UrlLocation == \"Body\"\r\n    and UrlDomain !endswith \"microsoft.com\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, Url, UrlDomain\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// in — multiple click action types\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType in (\"ClickBlocked\", \"ClickAllowed\")\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, ActionType, IsClickedThrough\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// in — multiple ZAP action types\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType in (\"Phish ZAP\", \"Spam ZAP\")\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, DeliveryLocation\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// and — risky attachment: executable AND inbound\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where FileExtension in (\".exe\", \".ps1\", \".vbs\")\r\n    and SenderFromAddress !endswith \"contoso.com\"\r\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, FileName, FileExtension\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"tilde\" name=\"tilde\"></a>\r\n## tilde ( ~ )\r\n\r\n- Case-insensitive equality comparison.\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Case-insensitive equality\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where SenderFromAddress =~ \"USER@CONTOSO.COM\"\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// in~ for case-insensitive list matching\r\nCloudAppEvents\r\n| where Application in~ (\"MICROSOFT SHAREPOINT ONLINE\", \"microsoft onedrive for business\", \"microsoft Teams\", \"Microsoft EXCHANGE Online\")\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Case-insensitive alert title match\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Title =~ \"suspicious sign-in activity\"\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, ServiceSource\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// in~ — case-insensitive severity filter\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Severity in~ (\"HIGH\", \"high\", \"High\")\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, Category\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Case-insensitive user lookup in IdentityInfo\r\nIdentityInfo\r\n| where AccountUpn =~ \"ADMIN@CONTOSO.COM\"\r\n| project AccountUpn, AccountDisplayName, Department, JobTitle, IsAccountEnabled",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// in~ — match Entra sign-in app names regardless of casing\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| where Application in~ (\"MICROSOFT TEAMS\", \"microsoft teams\", \"Microsoft Teams\")\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, IPAddress, Country\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// =~ on UrlDomain — case-insensitive domain match\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where UrlDomain =~ \"Contoso.COM\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, Url, UrlDomain\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// in~ — case-insensitive action type list match\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType in~ (\"clickblocked\", \"CLICKBLOCKED\")\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, ActionType\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// =~ on ActionType — case-insensitive post-delivery match\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType =~ \"phish zap\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, DeliveryLocation\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// =~ on FileType — case-insensitive match\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where FileType =~ \"PDF\"\r\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, FileName, FileType\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"project\" name=\"project\"></a>\r\n## project\r\n\r\n- Selects which columns to include in output.\r\n- Also used to rename columns.\r\n\r\n\r\n**How `project` works**\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25;\">\r\nBefore: All columns\r\n┌───────────┬─────────────┬───────────┬──────────┬─────────┐\r\n│ Timestamp │ Subject     │ Sender    │ Size     │ ...20+  │\r\n├───────────┼─────────────┼───────────┼──────────┼─────────┤\r\n│ 10:01     │ Invoice     │ a@ext.com │ 45000    │ ...     │\r\n│ 10:02     │ Meeting     │ b@int.com │ 12000    │ ...     │\r\n└───────────┴─────────────┴───────────┴──────────┴─────────┘\r\n                         │\r\n    | project Subject, Sender, Timestamp\r\n                         │\r\n                         ▼\r\nAfter: Only selected columns\r\n┌─────────────┬───────────┬───────────┐\r\n│ Subject     │ Sender    │ Timestamp │\r\n├─────────────┼───────────┼───────────┤\r\n│ Invoice     │ a@ext.com │ 10:01     │\r\n│ Meeting     │ b@int.com │ 10:02     │\r\n└─────────────┴───────────┴───────────┘\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailEvents\r\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, RecipientEmailAddress, Subject\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Rename columns for readability\r\nIdentityLogonEvents\r\n| project \r\n    SignInTime = Timestamp, \r\n    User = AccountUpn, \r\n    App = Application, \r\n    Country = Location\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Select key alert columns\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, Category, ServiceSource\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Rename sign-in columns for readable output\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| project\r\n    SignInTime   = Timestamp,\r\n    User         = AccountUpn,\r\n    App          = Application,\r\n    Location     = Country,\r\n    FailureCode  = ErrorCode\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Select key identity info columns\r\nIdentityInfo\r\n| project AccountUpn, AccountDisplayName, Department, JobTitle, City, Country, IsAccountEnabled\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Rename Teams message columns for clean output\r\nMessageEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project\r\n    EventTime  = Timestamp,\r\n    MessageId  = TeamsMessageId,\r\n    Sender     = SenderEmailAddress,\r\n    Verdict    = DeliveryAction,\r\n    Threat     = ThreatTypes\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Select alert evidence columns\r\nAlertEvidence\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project Timestamp, AlertId, EntityType, AccountUpn, RemoteIP, FileName, EvidenceRole\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Select key URL columns\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, Url, UrlDomain, UrlLocation\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Rename click columns for readable output\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project\r\n    ClickTime      = Timestamp,\r\n    User           = AccountUpn,\r\n    ClickedUrl     = Url,\r\n    WasBlocked     = ActionType,\r\n    ClickedThrough = IsClickedThrough\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Select key post-delivery columns\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, DeliveryLocation, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Select and rename attachment columns\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project\r\n    ReceivedTime = Timestamp,\r\n    Sender       = SenderFromAddress,\r\n    File         = FileName,\r\n    Extension    = FileExtension,\r\n    SizeMB       = round(FileSize / 1048576.0, 2)\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"project-away-project-reorder\" name=\"project-away-and-project-reorder\"></a>\r\n## project-away / project-reorder\r\n\r\n- `project-away`: Remove specific columns\r\n- `project-reorder`: Change column order\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Remove columns you don't need\r\nCloudAppEvents\r\n| project-away RawEventData, AdditionalFields\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// review column order\r\nIdentityLogonEvents\r\n| getschema ",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Reorder - put important columns first\r\nIdentityLogonEvents\r\n| project-reorder Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, Location\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Remove verbose columns from AlertEvidence\r\nAlertEvidence\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project-away AdditionalFields\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// review column order for EntraSignInEvents\r\nEntraSignInEvents | getschema",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Reorder Entra sign-in columns — most useful first\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| project-reorder Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, IPAddress, Country, ErrorCode\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Reorder AlertInfo — key context up front\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project-reorder Timestamp, Title, Severity, Category, ServiceSource\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// project-away verbose URL columns\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project-away ReportId\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// project-reorder — put user and URL first for readability\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project-reorder AccountUpn, Url, ActionType, Timestamp\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// project-reorder post-delivery events — action first\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project-reorder ActionType, ThreatTypes, Timestamp, NetworkMessageId\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// project-away ReportId from attachments — not needed for hunting\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| project-away ReportId, ThreatNames\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"distinct\" name=\"distinct\"></a>\r\n## distinct\r\n\r\n- Returns unique values, removing duplicates.\r\n- Great for finding \"what exists\" in your data.\r\n\r\n**How `distinct` works**\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25;\">\r\nBefore: Raw data with duplicates\r\n┌─────────────────┐\r\n│ SenderDomain    │\r\n├─────────────────┤\r\n│ gmail.com       │\r\n│ outlook.com     │\r\n│ gmail.com       │  <-- duplicate\r\n│ yahoo.com       │\r\n│ gmail.com       │  <-- duplicate\r\n│ outlook.com     │  <-- duplicate\r\n└─────────────────┘\r\n         │\r\n    | distinct SenderDomain\r\n         │\r\n         ▼\r\nAfter: Unique values only\r\n┌─────────────────┐\r\n│ SenderDomain    │\r\n├─────────────────┤\r\n│ gmail.com       │\r\n│ outlook.com     │\r\n│ yahoo.com       │\r\n└─────────────────┘\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "IdentityLogonEvents\r\n| distinct Application",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "CloudAppEvents\r\n| distinct Application",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique sender domains\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| distinct SenderFromDomain",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique applications in sign-in logs\r\nIdentityLogonEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| distinct Application",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique action types in CloudAppEvents\r\nCloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| distinct ActionType",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique file types in attachments\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| distinct FileType",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique URL domains in emails\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| distinct UrlDomain\r\n| take 50",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique applications where URLs were clicked\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| distinct Workload",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique post-delivery action types\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| distinct ActionType",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// project vs distinct\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(1d)\r\n| project InternetMessageId\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// project vs distinct\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(1d)\r\n| distinct InternetMessageId\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique alert severity levels\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| distinct Severity",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique alert categories\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| distinct Category",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique countries in Entra sign-in events\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| distinct Country",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique entity types in alert evidence\r\nAlertEvidence\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| distinct EntityType, Application",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Unique domains sent in Teams message URLs\r\nMessageUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| distinct UrlDomain\r\n| take 50",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"sort-by\" name=\"sort-by\"></a>\r\n## sort by\r\n\r\n- Orders rows by column(s).\r\n- `asc` = ascending (A→Z, 1→9), `desc` = descending (Z→A, 9→1)\r\n\r\n**How `sort by` works**\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25;\">\r\nBefore: Unsorted\r\n┌───────────┬─────────────┐\r\n│ Timestamp │ Subject     │\r\n├───────────┼─────────────┤\r\n│ 10:30     │ Meeting     │\r\n│ 09:15     │ Invoice     │\r\n│ 14:45     │ Report      │\r\n│ 11:00     │ Hello       │\r\n└───────────┴─────────────┘\r\n         │\r\n    | sort by Timestamp desc\r\n         │\r\n         ▼\r\nAfter: Newest first\r\n┌───────────┬─────────────┐\r\n│ Timestamp │ Subject     │\r\n├───────────┼─────────────┤\r\n│ 14:45     │ Report      │\r\n│ 11:00     │ Hello       │\r\n│ 10:30     │ Meeting     │\r\n│ 09:15     │ Invoice     │\r\n└───────────┴─────────────┘\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Most recent sign-ins first\r\nIdentityLogonEvents\r\n| sort by Timestamp desc\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Sort by multiple columns\r\nCloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| sort by AccountDisplayName asc // ignored\r\n| sort by Timestamp desc\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Sort by multiple columns\r\n// for each user, their newest event comes first, users grouped alphabetically\r\nCloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| sort by AccountDisplayName asc, Timestamp desc\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// top 10 largest attachments\nEmailAttachmentInfo\n| where Timestamp >= ago(14d)\n| extend\n    FileSizeKB = round(FileSize / 1024.0, 2),\n    FileSizeMB = round(FileSize / 1024.0 / 1024.0, 2)\n| project FileName, FileSize, FileSizeKB, FileSizeMB\n| sort by FileSize desc\n| take 10\n",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Most recent high-severity alerts first\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Severity == \"High\"\r\n| sort by Timestamp desc\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, Category\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Sort Entra sign-in failures — newest first\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| where ErrorCode != 0\r\n| sort by Timestamp desc\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, IPAddress, Country, ErrorCode\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Sort Teams message threats — newest first\r\nMessageEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ThreatTypes != \"\"\r\n| sort by Timestamp desc\r\n| project Timestamp, TeamsMessageId, SenderEmailAddress, DeliveryAction, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Sort URLs by domain then newest first\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| sort by UrlDomain asc, Timestamp desc\r\n| project Timestamp, UrlDomain, Url, UrlLocation\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Sort click events — most recent blocked clicks first\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType == \"ClickBlocked\"\r\n| sort by Timestamp desc\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Sort post-delivery events — newest ZAP first\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| sort by Timestamp desc\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"contains-has-startswith-endswith\" name=\"contains-has-startswith-endswith\"></a>\r\n## contains / has / startswith / endswith\r\n\r\n- `has` - Token match (faster, uses index)\r\n- `contains` - Substring match (slower)\r\n- `startswith` / `endswith` - Prefix/suffix match\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "CloudAppEvents\r\n| where ActionType has \"Create\"\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// has vs contains\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n// | where Url contains \"www.facebook\"\r\n| where Url has \"www.facebook\"",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// contains - substring\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where Subject contains \"invoice\"\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// contains - substring\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where Subject has \"invoice\"\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// contains - substring\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(14d)\r\n| where EmailDirection == \"Inbound\"\r\n// | where SenderFromDomain == \"contoso.com\"\r\n// | where RecipientDomain == \"fabrikam.com\"\r\n| where SenderDisplayName contains \"Claire\"",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(14d)\r\n| where EmailDirection == \"Inbound\"\r\n// | where SenderFromDomain == \"contoso.com\"\r\n// | where RecipientDomain == \"fabrikam.com\"\r\n| where SenderDisplayName has_any (\"Claire\",\"Rivera\")",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// startswith\r\nIdentityLogonEvents\r\n| where Application startswith \"Microsoft\"\r\n| distinct Application",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// has — fast token match on alert titles\r\nAlertInfo\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Title has \"sign\"\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, ServiceSource\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// has_any — alert categories related to credential attacks\r\nAlertInfo\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Category has_any (\"CredentialAccess\", \"InitialAccess\", \"Impact\")\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Category, Severity\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// contains — partial match on sign-in user agent string\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| where UserAgent contains \"python\"\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, IPAddress, UserAgent\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// startswith — find service principals by name prefix\r\nEntraSpnSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ServicePrincipalName startswith \"app-\"\r\n| project Timestamp, ServicePrincipalName, ApplicationId, IPAddress, ErrorCode\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// has on UrlDomain — token match for a domain keyword\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where UrlDomain has \"disney\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, Url, UrlDomain\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// contains on Url — substring scan for a path pattern\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Url contains \"/login\"\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, ActionType\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// has on ThreatTypes — token match\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ThreatTypes has \"Phish\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// has on FileName — find zip by extension token\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where FileName has \".zip\"\r\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, FileName, FileType\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"negation\" name=\"negation\"></a>\r\n## negation ( ! )\r\n\r\n- Adds `!` to string operators to negate them: `!contains`, `!has`, `!in`, `!startswith`, `!endswith`\r\n- For numeric or exact equality negation, use `!=` — covered in the [equality operators](#equality-operators) section.\r\n\r\n**Common negation operators**\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25;\">\r\n┌───────────────┬───────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────┐\r\n| Operator      | Negates       | Example                                    |\r\n├───────────────┼───────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────┤\r\n| !contains     | contains      | SenderDomain !contains \"contoso\"           |\r\n| !has          | has           | Subject !has \"invoice\"                     |\r\n| !in           | in            | Domain !in (\"contoso.com\", \"google.com\")   |\r\n| !startswith   | startswith    | App !startswith \"Microsoft\"                |\r\n| !endswith     | endswith      | FileName !endswith \".exe\"                  |\r\n└───────────────┴───────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────┘\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Exclude internal domains\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where SenderFromDomain !contains \"contoso.com\"\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// not from these domains\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where SenderFromDomain  !in (\r\n    \"contoso.com\", \r\n    \"starbucks.cafe\",\r\n    \"abc.com\"\r\n    )\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exclude a delivery action substring\r\nMessageEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where DeliveryAction !contains \"Delivered\"\r\n| project Timestamp, TeamsMessageId, SenderEmailAddress, DeliveryAction, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exclude emails where subject contains the token \"unsubscribe\"\r\n// Useful for filtering out marketing mail\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Subject !has \"unsubscribe\"\r\n| where EmailDirection == \"Inbound\"\r\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromDomain, Subject\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exclude apps that start with \"Microsoft\"\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Application !startswith \"Microsoft\"\r\n| distinct Application\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// find attachments that are NOT PDFs\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where FileName !endswith \".pdf\"\r\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, FileName, FileType\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exclude a list of known-safe alert categories\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Category !in (\"Impact\", \"ThreatManagement\")\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, Category\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exclude known safe domains from URL results\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where UrlDomain !has \"microsoft\"\r\n    and UrlDomain !has \"contoso\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, Url, UrlDomain\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exclude known-safe click actions\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType !in (\"ClickAllowed\")\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, ActionType\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// exclude automated remediation entries\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType !contains \"Auto\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"count\" name=\"count\"></a>\r\n## count\r\n\r\n- `| count` - Standalone operator that returns total row count.\r\n- Quick way to see how many rows match your filters.\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Simple count - total rows\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| count",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Count unique users\r\nCloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| distinct AccountDisplayName\r\n| count",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Count high-severity alerts in last 7 days\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where Severity == \"High\"\r\n| count",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Count failed Entra sign-ins in last 24h\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| where ErrorCode != 0\r\n| count",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Count Teams messages with threat detections this week\r\nMessageEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ThreatTypes != \"\"\r\n| count",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Count URLs from external domains in last 7 days\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where UrlDomain !endswith \"contoso.com\"\r\n| count",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Count blocked clicks in last 24h\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| where ActionType == \"ClickBlocked\"\r\n| count",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Count ZAP actions this week\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType has \"ZAP\"\r\n| count",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Count attachments with risky extensions this month\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| where FileExtension in (\".exe\", \".ps1\", \".vbs\", \".bat\", \".js\")\r\n| count",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"comparison-operators\" name=\"comparison-operators\"></a>\r\n## >, <, >=, <= (numeric comparisons)\r\n\r\n- For comparing **numeric** values: file sizes, counts, error codes, timestamps.\r\n- Different from `==` / `!=` which test for exact equality — see the [equality operators](#equality-operators) section.\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Files larger than 10MB\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(17d)\r\n| where FileSize > 10000000\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Emails with multiple attachments\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where AttachmentCount >= 3\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Sign-ins during off-hours (before 6am or after 8pm UTC)\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where hourofday(Timestamp) < 6 or hourofday(Timestamp) >= 20\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, Country, ErrorCode\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Sign-in failures — non-zero error codes only\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| where ErrorCode > 0\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, IPAddress, ErrorCode\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Alert evidence: IP-based entities only (EntityType is a string,\r\n// but RemotePort is numeric when populated)\r\nAlertEvidence\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where EntityType == \"Ip\"\r\n| project Timestamp, AlertId, RemoteIP, EvidenceRole\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Alerts fired in the last hour only\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(1h)\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, Category\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// URLs from large emails — message size > 5MB\r\n// Join EmailUrlInfo with EmailEvents on NetworkMessageId\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| join kind=inner (\r\n    EmailEvents\r\n    | where EmailSize > 5242880\r\n) on NetworkMessageId\r\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, Url, EmailSize\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// UrlClickEvents — clicks more than 3 seconds after email arrived\r\n// IsClickedThrough == true means user bypassed the warning\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where IsClickedThrough == true\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, ActionType\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// EmailPostDeliveryEvents — filter to recent ZAP actions\r\n// Timestamp comparison — last 4 hours\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(4h)\r\n| where ActionType has \"ZAP\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"ago\" name=\"time-and-ago\"></a>\r\n## ago()\r\n\r\n- `ago()` - Relative time from now\r\n- Time units: `d` (days), `h` (hours), `m` (minutes), `s` (seconds)\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Last 7 days\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(7d)\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Last 2 hours\r\nCloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(2h)\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Last 24 hours of Entra sign-in failures\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(24h)\r\n| where ErrorCode != 0\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Last 4 hours of high-severity alerts\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(4h)\r\n| where Severity == \"High\"\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, ServiceSource\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Last 48 hours of Teams message threats\r\nMessageEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(48h)\r\n| where ThreatTypes != \"\"\r\n| project Timestamp, TeamsMessageId, SenderEmailAddress, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Last 48 hours of URL click events\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(48h)\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, ActionType\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Last 14 days of email URL info\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(14d)\r\n| distinct UrlDomain\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Last 72 hours of post-delivery events\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(72h)\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Last 30 days — distinct risky attachment senders\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp >= ago(30d)\r\n| where FileExtension in (\".exe\", \".ps1\", \".vbs\")\r\n| distinct SenderFromAddress",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"between-datetime\" name=\"between-datetime\"></a>\r\n## between / datetime\r\n\r\n- Filter specific time ranges.\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Specific date range\r\nEmailEvents\r\n| where Timestamp between (datetime(2026-01-01) .. datetime(2026-01-07))\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Between 3 days ago and 1 day ago\r\nCloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp between (ago(3d) .. ago(1d))\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Specific date range for Entra sign-in events\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp between (datetime(2026-01-01) .. datetime(2026-01-07))\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, IPAddress, ErrorCode\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Alert window: between 2 days ago and 6 hours ago\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp between (ago(2d) .. ago(6h))\r\n| project Timestamp, Title, Severity, ServiceSource\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Teams message threats in a specific window\r\nMessageEvents\r\n| where Timestamp between (ago(3d) .. ago(1d))\r\n| where ThreatTypes != \"\"\r\n| project Timestamp, TeamsMessageId, SenderEmailAddress, ThreatTypes\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// URL clicks in a specific investigation window\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp between (datetime(2026-01-10T08:00:00Z) .. datetime(2026-01-10T18:00:00Z))\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, ActionType",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Post-delivery events in a specific incident window\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp between (ago(3d) .. ago(1d))\r\n| where ActionType has \"ZAP\"\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, ThreatTypes",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// EmailUrlInfo — URLs seen in a specific date range\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp between (datetime(2026-01-01) .. datetime(2026-01-31))\r\n| distinct UrlDomain\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// EmailAttachmentInfo — risky files in a specific window\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp between (ago(7d) .. ago(1d))\r\n| where FileExtension in (\".exe\", \".ps1\", \".vbs\")\r\n| project Timestamp, SenderFromAddress, FileName, FileExtension",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"time-formats\" name=\"time-formats\"></a>\r\n## Time Formats\r\n\r\n- KQL supports ISO8601 datetime.\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "print dt = datetime(2026-01-07T13:00:00Z)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "print pastWeek = ago(7d), pastHour = ago(1h), past30Min = ago(30m)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// ISO 8601 with timezone — common in audit and alert timestamps\r\nprint AlertTime = datetime(2026-01-15T09:30:00Z), WindowStart = datetime(2026-01-15T09:00:00Z)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Relative windows — common hunting patterns\r\nprint Last15m = ago(15m), LastHour = ago(1h), Last4h = ago(4h), Last24h = ago(24h), Last7d = ago(7d)",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Datetime arithmetic — compute a window from a known event time\r\nprint\r\n    IncidentStart  = datetime(2026-01-15T09:00:00Z),\r\n    TwoHoursLater  = datetime(2026-01-15T09:00:00Z) + 2h,\r\n    OneDayBefore   = datetime(2026-01-15T09:00:00Z) - 1d",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"now\" name=\"now-and-utc\"></a>\r\n## now()\r\n\r\n- `now()` returns current UTC time.\r\n- All Advanced Hunting timestamps are UTC.\r\n- Threat Explorer (UI) does detect timezone and display it in local timezone\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "print CurrentTime = now()",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// How long ago was each sign-in?\r\nIdentityLogonEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| extend HoursAgo = datetime_diff('hour', now(), Timestamp)\r\n| project Timestamp, HoursAgo, AccountUpn, Application\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// How long ago was each alert fired?\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\r\n| extend HoursAgo = datetime_diff('hour', now(), Timestamp)\r\n| project Timestamp, HoursAgo, Title, Severity\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// How many minutes ago did each sign-in failure occur?\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(2h)\r\n| where ErrorCode != 0\r\n| extend MinutesAgo = datetime_diff('minute', now(), Timestamp)\r\n| project Timestamp, MinutesAgo, AccountUpn, IPAddress, ErrorCode\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// How many hours ago was each blocked click?\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType == \"ClickBlocked\"\r\n| extend HoursAgo = datetime_diff(\"hour\", now(), Timestamp)\r\n| project HoursAgo, AccountUpn, Url, ActionType\r\n| sort by HoursAgo asc\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// How many hours since each ZAP action?\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType has \"ZAP\"\r\n| extend HoursAgo = datetime_diff(\"hour\", now(), Timestamp)\r\n| project HoursAgo, NetworkMessageId, ActionType, ThreatTypes\r\n| sort by HoursAgo asc\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// How many days since each risky attachment was seen?\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| where FileExtension in (\".exe\", \".ps1\", \".vbs\")\r\n| extend DaysAgo = datetime_diff(\"day\", now(), Timestamp)\r\n| project DaysAgo, SenderFromAddress, FileName, FileExtension\r\n| sort by DaysAgo asc\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// How long ago were external URLs last seen?\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(14d)\r\n| where UrlDomain !endswith \"microsoft.com\"\r\n| extend DaysAgo = datetime_diff(\"day\", now(), Timestamp)\r\n| project DaysAgo, UrlDomain, Url\r\n| sort by DaysAgo asc\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"top\" name=\"top\"></a>\r\n## top\r\n\r\n- Returns the top N rows sorted by a column.\r\n- Combines `sort by` and `take` in one operator.\r\n\r\n**How `top` works**\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25;\">\r\nBefore: Unsorted data\r\n┌─────────────────┬───────────┐\r\n│ SenderDomain    │ Count     │\r\n├─────────────────┼───────────┤\r\n│ gmail.com       │ 150       │\r\n│ outlook.com     │ 890       │\r\n│ yahoo.com       │ 45        │\r\n│ hotmail.com     │ 320       │\r\n│ aol.com         │ 12        │\r\n└─────────────────┴───────────┘\r\n              │\r\n    | top 3 by Count desc\r\n              │\r\n              ▼\r\nAfter: Top 3 by Count\r\n┌─────────────────┬───────────┐\r\n│ SenderDomain    │ Count     │\r\n├─────────────────┼───────────┤\r\n│ outlook.com     │ 890       │\r\n│ hotmail.com     │ 320       │\r\n│ gmail.com       │ 150       │\r\n└─────────────────┴───────────┘\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| summarize \n    EmailCount = count() \n    by SenderFromDomain\n| top 20 by EmailCount desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where ThreatTypes has_any (\"Phish\", \"Malware\")\n| summarize\n    ThreatEmailCount = count(), \n    DistinctRecipients = dcount(RecipientEmailAddress)\n    by SenderFromDomain\n| top 10 by ThreatEmailCount desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailAttachmentInfo\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| summarize\n    AttachmentCount = count(), \n    DistinctMessages = dcount(NetworkMessageId)\n    by FileType\n| top 10 by AttachmentCount desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "CloudAppEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType == \"FileUploaded\"\r\n| summarize\r\n    UploadCount = count(), \r\n    DistinctUsers = dcount(AccountObjectId)\r\n    by Application\r\n| top 10 by UploadCount desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Top 10 most triggered alert titles this week\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| summarize\r\n    AlertCount = count()\r\n    by Title\r\n| top 10 by AlertCount desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Top 10 apps with most Entra sign-in failures\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ErrorCode != 0\r\n| summarize\r\n    FailureCount   = count(),\r\n    DistinctUsers  = dcount(AccountUpn)\r\n    by Application\r\n| top 10 by FailureCount desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Top 10 Teams message senders with threat detections\r\nMessageEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ThreatTypes != \"\"\r\n| summarize\r\n    ThreatMessages = count(),\r\n    DistinctThreats = dcount(ThreatTypes)\r\n    by SenderEmailAddress\r\n| top 10 by ThreatMessages desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Top 10 most clicked URLs\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| summarize ClickCount = count() by Url\r\n| top 10 by ClickCount desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Top 10 post-delivery action types this month\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| summarize Count = count() by ActionType\r\n| top 10 by Count desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Top 10 URL domains seen in email\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| summarize Count = count() by UrlDomain\r\n| top 10 by Count desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Top 10 senders with risky attachments\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(30d)\r\n| where FileExtension in (\".exe\", \".ps1\", \".vbs\", \".bat\")\r\n| summarize Count = count() by SenderFromAddress\r\n| top 10 by Count desc",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"extend\" name=\"extend\"></a>\r\n## extend\r\n\r\n- Adds new calculated columns to your results.\r\n- Original columns are preserved.\r\n\r\n**How `extend` works**\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"background: transparent; padding: 0; margin: 0; font-family: 'JetBrainsMono Nerd Font', monospace; line-height: 1.25;\">\r\nBefore: Original columns\r\n┌─────────────┬──────────┐\r\n│ FileName    │ FileSize │  (bytes)\r\n├─────────────┼──────────┤\r\n│ dogs.pdf    │ 1048576  │\r\n│ cats.jpg    │ 524288   │\r\n└─────────────┴──────────┘\r\n              │\r\n    | extend FileSizeKB = FileSize / 1024\r\n    | extend FileSizeMB = FileSize / 1024 / 1024\r\n              │\r\n              ▼\r\nAfter: Original + new columns\r\n┌─────────────┬──────────┬────────────┬────────────┐\r\n│ FileName    │ FileSize │ FileSizeKB │ FileSizeMB │\r\n├─────────────┼──────────┼────────────┼────────────┤\r\n│ dogs.pdf    │ 1048576  │ 1024       │ 1          │\r\n│ cats.jpg    │ 524288   │ 512        │ 0.5        │\r\n└─────────────┴──────────┴────────────┴────────────┘\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Examples**",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Convert ; round by 2 decimal\r\nEmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| extend FileSizeKB = round(FileSize / 1024.0, 2)\r\n| extend FileSizeMB = round(FileSize / 1024.0 / 1024.0, 2)\r\n| project FileName, FileType, FileSize, FileSizeKB, FileSizeMB\r\n| sample 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailAttachmentInfo\r\n| extend FileNameLower = tolower(FileName)\r\n| project FileName, FileNameLower\r\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "EmailUrlInfo\r\n| extend DomainAndLocation = strcat(UrlDomain, \" (\", UrlLocation, \")\")\r\n| project DomainAndLocation\r\n| sample 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Add a readable severity tag to alert output\r\nAlertInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| extend SeverityTag = strcat(\"[\", Severity, \"] \", Title)\r\n| project Timestamp, SeverityTag, Category, ServiceSource\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Add a risk label based on Entra sign-in error code\r\nEntraSignInEvents\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| extend SignInResult = iff(ErrorCode == 0, \"Success\", strcat(\"Failure (\", tostring(ErrorCode), \")\"))\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Application, Country, SignInResult\r\n| take 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Combine Teams URL info into a display label\r\nMessageUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| extend UrlLabel = strcat(UrlDomain, \" | \", Url)\r\n| project Timestamp, TeamsMessageId, UrlLabel\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Add a location label to each URL\r\nEmailUrlInfo\r\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| extend UrlLabel = strcat(UrlDomain, \" (\", UrlLocation, \")\")\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, UrlLabel, Url\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Classify click risk level\r\nUrlClickEvents\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| extend RiskLevel = iff(ActionType == \"ClickBlocked\", \"High\", \"Low\")\r\n| project Timestamp, AccountUpn, Url, RiskLevel\r\n| take 10",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Add a human-readable action label to post-delivery events\r\nEmailPostDeliveryEvents\r\n// | where Timestamp > ago(7d)\r\n| where ActionType !in (\"Dynamic Delivery\", \"Manual Remediation\", \"\")\r\n| extend ActionLabel = strcat(ActionType, \" → \", ThreatTypes)\r\n| project Timestamp, NetworkMessageId, ActionLabel\r\n| sample 20",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"live-scenario-emailattachmentinfo\" name=\"live-scenario-emailattachmentinfo\"></a>\r\n## Live Scenario: EmailAttachmentInfo\r\n\r\n### Scenario\r\nYour security team received intelligence that threat actors are using `.iso`, `.vhd`, and `.img` files to deliver malware.\r\n\r\n### Your Mission\r\nFind all emails from the last 7 days with these potentially dangerous attachment types.\r\n\r\n### Skills Tested\r\n- `where` with time filter\r\n- `in` operator\r\n- `project` for clean output",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Try\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"live-scenario-emailevents\" name=\"live-scenario-emailevents\"></a>\r\n## Live Scenario: EmailEvents\r\n\r\n### Scenario\r\nUsers are complaining about spam. Management wants a list of external domains sending email to the organization.\r\n\r\n### Your Mission\r\nFind all unique external sender domains from the last 7 days, excluding known trusted domains, sorted alphabetically.\r\n\r\n### Skills Tested\r\n- `where` with time and direction filter\r\n- `distinct` for unique values\r\n- negation with `!in` to exclude trusted domains\r\n- `sort by`",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Try\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\r\n\r\n---",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"live-scenario-cloudappevents\" name=\"live-scenario-cloudappevents\"></a>\r\n## Live Scenario: CloudAppEvents\r\n\r\n### Scenario\r\nYour manager wants a quick overview of user activity in cloud applications.\r\n\r\n### Your Mission\r\nFind all unique applications and action types users are performing, filtered to the last 7 days.\r\n\r\n### Skills Tested\r\n- `CloudAppEvents` table\r\n- `where` with time filter\r\n- `distinct` for unique values\r\n- `sort by`",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// Try\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
            "outputs": []
