        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"common-gotchas-tips\" name=\"common-gotchas-tips\"></a>\n## Common Gotchas & Tips\n\n### 1. `has` vs `contains` — Performance Matters\n\n- `has` uses the **term index** — fast whole-word/token match\n- `contains` does a **full substring scan** — checks every character of every string\n- Rule of thumb: use `has` unless you specifically need mid-word matching\n\nThe performance gap widens dramatically on large tables like `EmailEvents`.",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// FAST — has uses the term index (whole-word token match)\n// \"invoice\" must appear as a standalone word/token in the subject\nEmailEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where Subject has \"invoice\"\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// SLOWER — contains does a full substring scan on every row\n// Use this only when you need to match mid-word (e.g. \"inv\" inside \"invoice\")\nEmailEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where Subject contains \"invoice\"\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"2-case-sensitivity\" name=\"2-case-sensitivity\"></a>\n### 2. Case Sensitivity\n\n- `==` is **case-sensitive** — `\"gmail.com\"` ≠ `\"Gmail.com\"`\n- `=~` is **case-insensitive** — use when you can't guarantee casing\n- `has` is case-insensitive by default\n- `has_cs` is the case-sensitive version of `has`",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// GOTCHA: == is case-sensitive — this will return no results\n// \"GMAIL.COM\" does not equal \"gmail.com\"\nEmailEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\n| where SenderFromDomain == \"GMAIL.COM\"\n| take 1",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// FIX: use =~ for case-insensitive comparison\nEmailEvents\n| where Timestamp > ago(1d)\n| where SenderFromDomain =~ \"GMAIL.COM\"\n| take 1",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"3-has-wont-match-partial-words\" name=\"3-has-wont-match-partial-words\"></a>\n### 3. `has` won't match partial words\n\n`has` matches on whole tokens. If the word you're looking for is a substring of a larger word, `has` will miss it. Use `contains` in that case (and accept the performance trade-off).",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// GOTCHA: has \"phish\" does NOT match \"phishing\"\n// The token in the string is \"phishing\" — \"phish\" is not a standalone token\nAlertInfo\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where Title has \"phish\"       // misses \"phishing\", \"phished\"\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "code",
            "source": "// FIX: use contains when you need partial/substring matching\n// Accepts the slower scan in exchange for broader matching\nAlertInfo\n| where Timestamp > ago(7d)\n| where Title contains \"phish\"  // matches \"phish\", \"phishing\", \"phished\"\n| take 5",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "<a id=\"4-data-retention\" name=\"4-data-retention\"></a>\n### 4. Data Retention\n\nAdvanced Hunting retains data for **30 days** by default. Queries using `ago(31d)` or longer will return no results — not an error, just an empty result set. If you see an unexpectedly empty result, check your time window first.",
            "outputs": []
        },
        {
            "kind": "markdown",
            "source": "[back to top](#kql-for-email-security-beginner-series)\n\n---",
            "outputs": []
        }
